The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) on Monday received the report of the Ekiti State Three-man Ad-hoc Delegate Ward Congress conducted on Saturday, January 15, 2022. The PDP, in a statement by its spokesman, Hon. Debo Ologunagba also received petitions and complaints from stakeholders on Congress. The NWC has assured that the report as well as the petitions and complaints will be comprehensively reviewed while all concerns raised will be carefully considered for amicable resolution in the overall interest of the Party. Ayu Vows To Probe PDP Past Administrations Over Unaccounted… 2023: PDP Must Wage War Against Enemies Within To Bounce Back The NWC urged all governorship aspirants, critical stakeholders and teeming members of “our Party in Ekiti State to remain calm, united and focused for the task ahead.”